Center: Center of Nuclear Physics Data, Russian Federal Nuclear Center (VNIIEF), Sarov, Russia
title: Investigation of elastic and inelastic scattering of protons from the nucleus Ne-22.

x4freetext: Investigation of elastic and inelastic scattering of
protons from the nucleus Ne-22.
From compiler: Partial reactions in subs 3-8 are not
"classical partial" reactions, as only the first
excitation level is energetically possible for them
at an incident energy used (1.5-2.5 MeV). These
reactions may be considered as total inelastic
processes.

reacs.QuantHlp: Differential c/s with respect to angle

x4freetext: Protons were detected by two semi-conductor
detectors RCA C-3-75-2. One of them placed at 135
degr. was used as monitor. The proton collimator in
front of the movable detector consisted of a slit
4x18 mm2 and a diaphragm 6 mm in diameter. They were
60 and 120 mm apart from the centre of the chamber,
respectively.
Special target chamber was used. The volume of the
chamber was separated from the vacuum of the
accelerating tube with a mica foil 0.5 mu-m thick. The
chamber was filled with neon (96% 22Ne) at 7 mm Hg
pressure.

x4freetext: Data on total inelastic process are given.
The gamma-rays were detected by two 75 x 75mm
NaI(Tl) crystals with the photomultipliers of the type
Du Mond 6362. The movable crystal as well as the
monitor were 120 mm apart from the centre of the
target. The monitor was at the angle of 90 degr. with
respect to the proton beam direction.
A cylindrical chamber 15 mm in diameter filled with
neon at 8 mm Hg pressure was used. The volume of the
chamber was separated from the accelerator tube by a
mica foil with thickness 0.5 mu-m.
